.Dd October 16, 2017
.Dt BHNDB_PCI 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm bhndb_pci
.Nd Broadcom Home Networking Division PCI host bridge driver
.Sh SYNOPSIS
To compile this driver into the kernel, add the following lines to the
kernel configuration file:
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
.Cd "device bhnd"
.Cd "device bhndb"
.Cd "device bhndb_pci"
.Cd "device pci"
.Ed
.Pp
To load the driver as a module at boot, add this line to
.Xr loader.conf 5 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
bhndb_pci_load="YES"
.Ed
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
driver provides
.Xr bhndb 4
support for the PCI and PCIe host bridge cores found in Broadcom Home Networking
Division's wireless chipsets and network adapters.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr bhnd 4 ,
.Xr bhndb 4 ,
.Xr bwn 4 ,
.Xr intro 4 ,
.Xr pci 4
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
device driver first appeared in
.Fx 11.0 .
